<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-058-301 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 441 549</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Sept 16 1991 v36 n19 p204(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Relay has electrically resettable fuse. (Design Ideas)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ochi, Sam.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An intelligent, completely isolated, solid-state ac relay that isequipped with a resettable 10 amp electronic fuse can switch 6kW(600 volts ac at 10 amps).andP;  A five-volt signal from a systemcontroller or a manual switch applied to the input voltage turnsthe relay on.andP;  The relay is then able to turn itself off, turn onLED and set a flag within one microsecond of sensing a shortcircuit.andP;  This relay can complete an on/off cycle in less than onemicrosecond at repetition rates reaching 50KHz.andP;  This cycle typeis useful in beginning extremely inductive loads.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     RelaysCircuit designSystem DesignSwitchesCircuit Components.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Intelligent, fully isolated, solid-state ac relay. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>